{"name": "ecodonut", "metadata": {"name": "ecodonut", "version": "1.0.3", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["geopandas", "numpy", "pandas", "matplotlib", "mapclassify", "folium", "tqdm", "dask", "networkx", "loguru"], "summary": null, "upload_time": 1732549247}, "documentation": ["# EcoDonut\n\n\u0411\u0438\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043e\u0442\u0435\u043a\u0430 \u0434\u043b\u044f \u0440\u0430\u0441\u0447\u0451\u0442\u0430 \u044d\u043a\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043a\u0430\u0440\u043a\u0430\u0441\u0430 \u0438\u0441\u043f\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0437\u0443\u0435\u043c\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u043f\u043b\u0430\u0442\u0444\u043e\u0440\u043c\u0435 \u0418\u0414\u0423\n\n## \u041a\u0430\u043a \u044d\u0442\u043e \u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0430\u0435\u0442\n\n[\u041e\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u044b \u0431\u0438\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043e\u0442\u0435\u043a\u0438](https://github.com/DDonnyy/EcoDonut/wiki/\u041e\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435-\u0430\u043b\u0433\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0442\u043c\u0430-\u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u044b-\u0431\u0438\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043e\u0442\u0435\u043a\u0438-Ecodonut-(RUS))\n\n### \u041a\u0430\u043a \u0438\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0440\u043f\u0440\u0435\u0442\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u0442\u044c \u0440\u0435\u0437\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0430\u0442\u044b:\n\n| name                     | type              | layer_impact | source         | color(optional) |\n|--------------------------|-------------------|--------------|----------------|-----------------|\n| ('\u041e\u0437\u0435\u0440\u043e', '\u0421\u0432\u0430\u043b\u043a\u0430')      | ('water', 'dump') | -5           | (False, False) | #d93429         |\n| ('\u0417\u0430\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0430', '\u0414\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0433\u0430')   | ('water', 'road') | -3           | (False, True)  | #fdb96a         |\n| ('\u0420\u0435\u043a\u0430', '\u0417\u0435\u043b\u0451\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0437\u043e\u043d\u0430') | ('water', 'dump') | 3            | (True, True)   | #bfe47a         |\n\n\u0412 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043d \u0441\u0440\u0435\u0437 \u0440\u0435\u0437\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0435\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043d\u0435\u043a\u043e\u0442\u043e\u0440\u044b\u0445 \u0441\u043b\u043e\u0451\u0432 \u0432\u043b\u0438\u044f\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043e\u0431\u044c\u0435\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u0440\u0430\u0437\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0442\u0438\u043f\u0430.\n\n### \u0420\u0435\u0437\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0430\u0442 \u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u044b \u0431\u0438\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043e\u0442\u0435\u043a\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0435 \u041b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u043d\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438\n![image](https://github.com/DDonnyy/EcoDonut/assets/63115678/7c005ccd-74b8-4756-86f4-84f556f19215)\n\n#### \u0411\u0430\u0437\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0435 [\u043f\u0440\u0438\u043c\u0435\u0440\u044b](./example) \u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u044b \u0441 \u0431\u0438\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043e\u0442\u0435\u043a\u043e\u0439 \n\n### \u0420\u0435\u0437\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0430\u0442 \u0441\u0438\u043c\u0443\u043b\u044f\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0437\u0430\u0433\u0440\u044f\u0437\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0432\u043e\u0434\u044b \u043e\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u043c\u044b\u0448\u043b\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043e\u0431\u044a\u0435\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u043f\u043e \u0421\u0430\u043d\u043a\u0442-\u041f\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0431\u0443\u0440\u0433\u0443, \u043d\u0430\u0445\u043e\u0434\u044f\u0449\u0438\u0445\u0441\u044f \u0440\u044f\u0434\u043e\u043c \u0441 \u0440\u0435\u043a\u0430\u043c\u0438.\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a51e82a7-7e8d-433b-bb9d-2540b7230acd)\n"], "modules": [{"name": "ecodonut.river_graph", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "ecodonut.river_graph.construct_water_graph", "xref": {"fqname": "ecodonut.river_graph.graph_builder.construct_water_graph", "project": null}}, {"name": "ecodonut.river_graph.simulate_spill", "xref": {"fqname": "ecodonut.river_graph.spill_sim.simulate_spill", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "ecodonut.river_graph.spill_sim", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "ecodonut.river_graph.spill_sim.simulate_spill", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "pollution_sources", "type": {"name": "gpd.GeoDataFrame", "xref": {"fqname": "geopandas.GeoDataFrame", "project": "geopandas"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "river_graph", "type": {"name": "nx.DiGraph", "xref": {"fqname": "networkx.DiGraph", "project": "networkx"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "min_dist_to_river", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "pollution_column", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "gpd.GeoDataFrame", "xref": {"fqname": "geopandas.GeoDataFrame", "project": "geopandas"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Simulate the spread of pollution in a river network, based on proximity to pollution sources and pollutant levels.\n\nThis function identifies pollution sources that are within a specified minimum distance from a river network,\ncalculates how much pollution remains along each edge in the river network, and aggregates the results into\npolygons representing affected areas with pollution values.\n\nArgs:\n    pollution_sources (gpd.GeoDataFrame): A GeoDataFrame containing the locations and pollution values of sources.\n    river_graph (nx.DiGraph): A directed graph representing the river network, with nodes and edges. The graph must\n        contain a 'crs' attribute indicating the coordinate reference system.\n    min_dist_to_river (float, optional): The maximum distance between pollution sources and river nodes for\n        pollution to be considered in the simulation. Default is 100.\n    pollution_column (str, optional): The name of the column in `pollution_sources` that specifies pollution values.\n        Default is \"pollution\".\n\nReturns:\n    gpd.GeoDataFrame: A GeoDataFrame containing polygons representing areas affected by pollution. Each polygon\n    has an attribute `remain`, which indicates the pollution concentration within that area."]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "ecodonut", "documentation": ["EcoDonut\n========\n\nEcoDonut is a Python package for the creation Eco-Frames and water graphs.\n\nHomepage https://github.com/DDonnyy/EcoDonut."], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "ecodonut.__version__", "xref": {"fqname": "ecodonut._version.VERSION", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "ecodonut._version", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "ecodonut._version.VERSION", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "ecodonut.eco_frame.output", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "ecodonut.eco_frame.output.value_to_color", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "eco_frame", "type": {"name": "EcoFrame", "xref": {"fqname": "ecodonut.eco_frame.EcoFrame", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "color_column", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "negative_minmax", "type": {"name": "tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "positive_minmax", "type": {"name": "tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "EcoFrame", "xref": {"fqname": "ecodonut.eco_frame.EcoFrame", "project": null}